### Affected Package
The issue is caused by Angular routing

### Is this a regression?
Yes it used to work with Angular 8. And Angular 8 websites are still working on the same machine.

### Description
I start a new Angular project using "ng new ProjectName". I add a new module with "ng g m AuthenticationModule". and add the module to the routing like this:

```
const routes: Routes = [
  { path: '', loadChildren: () => import('./authentication/authentication.module').then(module => module.AuthenticationModule) }
];

@NgModule({
  imports: [RouterModule.forRoot(routes)],
  exports: [RouterModule]
})
export class AppRoutingModule { }
```

This causes the project to crash in the browser!!

